5
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:24,789
? It's a mad, mad, mad...

6
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,996
<i>(car horn sounds repeatedly)</i>

7
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,356
<i>(tyres screech and horn blares)</i>

8
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:42,436
<i>(horn stíll blaríng repeatedly)</i>

9
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,155
Whoa!

10
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,999
Did you see the way
he went sailing right out there?

11
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:22,999
- He just went sailing out there.
- It was terrible. Just terrible.

12
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:27,238
- He must've been doin' over 80.
- An ambulance. We oughta call one.

13
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:33,156
- Oh, look at that car!
- He must've gone by you doin' 90mph.

14
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,157
I wasn't doing... He was passing me!

15
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:39,034
- I never saw such a crazy guy in my life!
- Let's get down there!

16
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:42,636
- We're goin' down there.
- Russell, remember your condition.

17
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,671
Achhh!

18
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,872
Boy, the way he just sailed out there!

19
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:51,235
Look out, look out, look out, look out.

20
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,755
- There's nobody in the car!
- Huh?

21
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,836
- What do you mean?
- There he is!

22
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,036
Holy smoke!

23
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:09,356
- How about that? This guy is still alive.
- Is he hurt?

24
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,357
Maybe we oughta call an ambulance.

25
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:15,155
I don't know how he survived,
the way he went sailing right out there.

26
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:19,353
Look, I'm not a doctor, but I have
some medical experience. I'm a dentist.

27
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,835
Do you think you're hurt... real bad?

28
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,672
Is he kiddin'?

29
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,870
Hold on. We'll get you to a hospital.

30
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,515
You move me, I'll break up in little pieces.

31
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,632
But what a deal!

32
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,035
Look, there's this dough, see?

33
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:39,994
There's all this dough! 350 Gs!

34
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:42,076
Do you hear what I'm sayin'?

35
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,760
350 Gs!

36
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:49,798
In the park, in Rosita.
Rosita Beach State Park.

37
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:52,878
Just south of Dago in Santa Rosita.

38
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,840
It's in this box, buried under this...

39
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,916
<i>(coughs)</i>

40
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,551
...buried under this big W.

41
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:04,638
You'll see it! You'll see it under this...

42
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,751
...under this big W.

43
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:09,235
You can't miss it! A big...

44
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,873
...a big W!

45
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,913
And it's been there...
it's been layin' there for 15 years!

46
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,430
- We oughta get him outta here.
- He's very sick. He may die.

47
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:21,233
Listen. I tell ya I'm givin' it to ya.

48
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,999
And don't let 'em kid ya.
Don't let 'em kid ya.

49
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:28,796
Don't let 'em give you the business, see?
Because it was mine, and I paid for it.

50
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,071
Paid for every lousy buck of it! Ya hear?

51
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,998
But watch out. Watch out for the bulls.

52
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:39,079
Lousy, stinkin' bulls are everywhere.

53
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,270
Bulls all over the place.

54
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,470
You just drive down and dig it up.

55
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:46,878
Dig it all up! <i>(coughs)</i>

56
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:53,514
And then... And then you fix yourselves
all up. Fix yourselves all up.

57
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:57,519
Walk down the street like a king,
back to the old neighbourhood.

58
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:00,234
See the fellas, the dames...

59
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:03,319
The dames, all with a big hello...

60
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,878
...a big hello for old Smiler.

61
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,476
"Good old Smiler."

62
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:13,397
"Everybody's friend."

63
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,670
Everybody's...

64
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:25,348
- Aunt Belle, I didn't mean to do it!
- Holy mackerel! Take it easy, mister.

65
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:29,314
Please! Please say it don't make
any difference, Aunt Belle!

66
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,749
Please! You gotta say it!

67
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:35,316
You gotta tell me
it don't make any difference!

68
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,957
For heaven's sake, tell him!

69
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,150
It... It don't make any difference.

70
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:05,039
That guy is dead. You better believe it.

71
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:09,358
Oh, I believe it. But if he jumps up again
like he did before, I'm gettin' outta here.

72
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:13,678
- Boy, what a routine he went through.
- Somebody oughta cover him up.

73
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,589
Don't look at me, pal.
All I got is this sweater.

74
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,790
Never mind. I got a blanket in the truck.

75
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:23,710
- D'you think it was true, what he told us?
- No, he was just ravin', man. He flipped.

76
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:29,392
Hey, this must be the police. You think we
oughta tell 'em what he was talkin' about?

77
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:32,592
No. They'll ask us questions.
We'll be here all day.

78
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:37,271
- We gotta be in Vegas this afternoon.
- I got a van of furniture to get to Yuma.

79
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:40,073
My wife and I are
on a second honeymoon and...

80
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,988
My wife is up there with her mother,
and we're on our way to Lake Mead.

81
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:47,112
What's all the arguing about?
We'll just clam up...

82
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,595
...and this way, we get outta here.

83
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:53,319
Uh, are you a police officer? I...

84
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,836
Yeah!

85
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:11,631
- How long ago did this happen?
- About five minutes ago, Officer.

86
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,276
Did any of you actually see it happen?

87
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:18,359
- Well, uh, he passed me on a curve and...
- Did anybody actually see it?

88
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:22,553
Well, he was passing me when he sailed
right out there. Right up there.

89
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:26,468
- Who was the first down to him?
- Well, we all... <i>(all talk together)</i>

90
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,318
Was he dead?

91
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,396
Was he already dead?

92
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:34,312
I said, was he already dead
when you got down here?

93
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,111
Practically.

94
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,629
He was still alive? Did he say anything?

95
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,991
Did he say anything before he died?

96
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:47,237
- What about?
- What do you mean, what about?!

97
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:50,432
Did he say anything
or didn't he say anything?

98
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,038
Well...

99
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,550
- He...
- He was raving, Officer.

100
00:10:56,680 --> 00:11:00,514
- What about, raving?
- He said... What he said was sort of...

101
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,710
- It was sort of...
- Embarrassing.

102
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,796
What was? Come on, come on.

103
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:08,480
He thought that this fella was his aunt.

104
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,591
- His aunt?
- Yeah, his Aunt Belle.

105
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,836
He must've had an aunt named Aunt Belle.

106
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,036
All right!

107
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:18,357
Did he make any kind of statement?
Any last messages?

108
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:22,268
- He didn't make that clear, at all.
- No, he didn't make anything clear.

109
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,551
- Look, Officer, can we get going?
- Just a minute, just a minute.

110
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,989
I'd better get your details, just in case.

111
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,190
My wife and I don't know
where we'll be...

112
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:33,232
I don't know if we can stick around.
We're doin' Las Vegas.

113
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:36,113
We don't know how long
we're gonna stay or...

114
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:38,834
I got this van of furniture.
I gotta get to Yuma...

115
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:42,350
Be reasonable, Officer. We stopped
to help the guy. We was too late.

116
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,836
- So let us get outta here, OK?
- We've got our own lives to live.

117
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:49,236
- Like, we ain't had breakfast yet.
- All right, take it easy.

118
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,715
I'm gonna have to get <i>your</i> name anyway.

119
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,636
Hold it.

120
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,597
Me?

121
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:01,076
- Why?
- In case the coroner wants a statement.

122
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:05,596
J Russell Finch,
2790 Penrose Boulevard, Fresno.

123
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:09,713
I won't be home for a couple of weeks,
but you can get me through my office.

124
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:13,879
- Where is your office?
- The Pacific Edible Seaweed Company.

125
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,753
It's in Fresno. You can
call me through my secretary.

126
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,155
- The ambulance is on its way.
- On its way.

127
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,236
- Is he dead?
- Yeah.

128
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,635
We'd better shift those cars
from the curve.

129
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:29,709
I guess that's all we can get from this
group. Thank you, gentlemen, very much.

130
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,157
Well...

131
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,669
There's an unexpected twist for you.

132
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,758
They're not gonna like this
down at Santa Rosita.

133
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:46,996
- Culpeper's gonna scream.
- Yeah.

134
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:50,192
- Say, we'd better get our story straight.
- What story?

135
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:54,438
He woke up as usual. He started driving.
He stopped at a place for breakfast.

136
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,994
He went to the gents.
He climbed out the window.

137
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:00,829
So what? Not even Culpeper will say
we should've been in there with him.

138
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:04,953
The thing that got me was the way
he went sailing right out there.

139
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:08,152
If I have to climb much more,
I'll be layin' down there with him.

140
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,236
Poor soul.

141
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,716
<i>(all)</i> Well...

142
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,274
Melville, what happened?

143
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,631
We couldn't do anything.
Just nothing we could do. Come on.

144
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,716
<i>(older woman)</i> Well?

145
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:31,634
- It was a terrible thing.
- Oh, Russell, I feel sick.

146
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:35,878
- Easy, honey. These things happen.
- What kind of an attitude is that?

147
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,278
The whole country is full of people
who, when these things happen...

148
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,119
...say "These things happen."
That's why they happen!

149
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:46,949
- Let's try not to get upset.
- Come on, Russell.

150
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,230
We gotta have control
of what happens to us!

151
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:52,079
If we left it up to you,
we'd never hear the last of it!

152
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:56,398
- <i>(woman contínues to rant)</i>
- <i>(Russell)</i> You're right, you're right.

153
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:03,352
And do you know what all those halfwit
morons up in Sacramento do about it?

154
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:06,870
They just sit there,
with their big feet up on their big desks...

155
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,639
...and milk 15 million people
of as much graft as...

156
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:13,878
Listen. I'm sorry to interrupt,
but I've gotta say something.

157
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,912
- What's the matter, Melville?
- I'm watching something.

158
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:20,794
Hey, Benjy, turn around.
Sit still. Play it straight.

159
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,672
They can't kid me. They all went for it.

160
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,916
Yeah? So what are you
gonna do now, huh?

161
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:29,591
I want you to tell me everything
that man told you, word for word!

162
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,836
But do you think he really meant it?

163
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:37,235
Monica, I don't know about anybody else
but some of 'em believed it...

164
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,713
...like those two back there.

165
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,592
Don't look over there!

166
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:43,951
I know where it is. It's under a big W,
he said. Under a big W.

167
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,355
Like a windmill or
a waterfall or something.

168
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,119
Ooh, I hope it's not under a waterfall.

169
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,595
Please, think of something
that starts with a W.

170
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:52,994
Wealth.

171
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,076
Which.

172
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,831
Where. Work! That's it: Work.
I gotta work on where it is.

173
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:03,078
Dr Carroll said Russell
was to have no undue excitement...

174
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,395
...for two weeks because of his condition.

175
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:08,432
That's why we came on this trip -
so Russell could just relax.

176
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:12,109
- He should have told the police.
- What's the police got to do with it?

177
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:18,190
- Mother, they were chasing the man.
- Why shouldn't they? He was speeding!

178
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:21,869
- I'm only thinking of Russell's condition.
- His financial condition.

179
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,554
Because that's the only
condition that he has.

180
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:28,309
Emmeline, do you know exactly why
your husband had a nervous breakdown?

181
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:32,831
It's because he has sunk $40,000 -
including $15,000 of <i>my</i> money -

182
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:36,191
...into a company that makes
seaweed for people to eat!

183
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:39,312
And not only does nobody like it,
but it costs over $4 a can!

184
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:41,431
- Yeah, but...
- Yeah, but what?

185
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:45,792
Most people like it, and I like it, and
I'm workin' hard to keep the cost down.

186
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:51,278
Yeah, like the day that you ran out of your
office and stood in the street screaming!

187
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,879
- Mother!
- Emmeline, shut up!

188
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,592
- But, Mother...
- And you too!

189
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:58,235
Maybe he was playing
some kind of a trick on everybody.

190
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:02,990
- He might have been a practical joker.
- Oh, Monica... Practical...

191
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:06,635
What kind of a man would play
a practical joke on complete strangers...

192
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,320
...with every bone in his body broken?

193
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:12,352
- Watch! Watchtower!
- No.

194
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:15,358
- Wall. Walnut tree!
- No, no!

195
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,515
- Walnuts!
- No!

196
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,392
- In bags.
- No!

197
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:22,431
Why are we doing only 35?
Step on it and see what happens!

198
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,790
- Mother.
- They'll all see what we're doing.

199
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:29,277
- Go ahead. What have you got to lose?
- Mother, he's not that good a driver.

200
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,589
Aha.

201
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,630
Aha!

202
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,836
Gonna leave the big boy behind, huh?

203
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:51,716
<i>(tyres screech)</i>

204
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,110
What are you doing?
Why are we slowing down?

205
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:05,629
It's no use. We can't lose 'em this way.

206
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,990
Oh, the inside of my stomach!

207
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,795
What's that idiot in the truck tryin' to do?

208
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,911
What is he doin' back there?

209
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:29,796
I bet he's runnin' out of gas. Good!

210
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,958
- What happened to you?
- Havin' trouble with your engine?

211
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:22,992
- What'd you do, run out of gas?
- Did ya bend your tailpipe?

212
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:26,032
Oh, no. It was just one of my tyres.

213
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:28,549
I thought... Aw, shucks.

214
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:31,433
OK, so I was tryin' to... Oh, rats.

215
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:34,074
Look, I think we're making
a very big mistake.

216
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,236
- I absolutely agree.
- So?

217
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:39,750
- It's silly, running around like this.
- We're gettin' nowhere.

218
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:40,869
He's right.

219
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:45,471
So why don't we just discuss this thing
and reason something out calmly...

220
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,828
- I'm with you.
- Fine.

221
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,190
...and we can come to some conclusion.

222
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:51,151
- Yeah, let's do that.
- <i>(car horn)</i>

223
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:55,751
Yeah. That way nobody'll have
an advantage on one another. It's fair.

224
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:59,839
- We better get the cars off that curve.
- Yeah. Let's talk over there.

225
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,076
- OK.
- Fine. See you over there.

226
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,156
Over there. Over there.

227
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,396
You're through to Homicide.

228
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,396
Santa Rosita Police Station.

229
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:15,518
Detective Division?
