- A lift?

447
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:37,638
Of course! I should be
absolutely delighted!

448
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:42,392
Oh, upsy-daisy. I'm afraid
you caught me on the hop there.

449
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:45,717
- Madam, do be careful of the cactus...
- Oh!

450
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:48,035
I say, I'm most frightfully sorry.

451
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:51,709
You see, I've been gathering
some samples of desert flora.

452
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:55,276
- Where shall I put this?
- <i>(sníggers)</i> Oh, boy.

453
00:34:57,400 --> 00:35:00,233
- Good morning. Good morning.
- Morning.

454
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,828
It certainly is. Look,
we've got to get to a phone.

455
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,598
Of course. With pleasure.

456
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:08,030
I say, jolly nasty accident there.
Jolly lucky nobody was hurt.

457
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:11,391
Where did you get that funny accent?
Are you from Harvard?

458
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:14,114
Harvard? Oh, rather not. I'm English.

459
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:16,913
- Sounds so foreign.
- Really?

460
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:21,352
Oh, we haven't introduced ourselves.
I'm Algernon Hawthorne. Colonel.

461
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:24,631
- You're a colonel?
- Well, lieutenant colonel, actually.

462
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:29,390
My name is Finch. This is my wife and
this is my mother-in-law, Mrs Marcus.

463
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:32,034
Oh, do stuff those things
in the back, will you?

464
00:35:32,160 --> 00:35:34,230
Cactus is rather a hobby of mine.

465
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:37,318
Spent the last ten days
gathering some for my collection.

466
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:39,510
Nothing spectacular, actually.

467
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:42,871
<i>Cereus, Echínocactus, Opuntía,</i>
and that sort of thing.

468
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,355
Been enjoying a spot of leave
from Vandenberg.

469
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:49,393
- From what?
- Vandenberg. The missile place.

470
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:52,637
Been attached there for the last
ten months. Liaison work.

471
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:55,149
All very hush-hush and whoosh-whoosh.

472
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:58,636
That sort of thing, you know.

473
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:02,636
Please, will you look at the road?

474
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,076
Yes. Whoosh-whoosh.

475
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:12,432
- Don't stop! Keep moving!
- Mother!

476
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:15,358
- Shouldn't we stop...
- He's the lout that ran into us!

477
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,674
Keep moving!

478
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:27,711
Melville, I just won't fly
in this old... Listen to it!

479
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,876
Just look at how it's shuddering!

480
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:33,515
Can't we just go on with our second
honeymoon and forget all about this?

481
00:36:33,640 --> 00:36:36,871
Honey, please. Darling,
believe me, everything is all right.

482
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,116
You think I'd take a chance with you?

483
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:43,711
If there was any danger in flying in this...
This is a plane that's really built...

484
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,796
Look, when was this plane built?

485
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:48,878
- 1916.
- 1916.

486
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:52,913
1916. I mean, these planes
are tried and true.

487
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:55,713
There's nothing experimental
about these planes.

488
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,990
So come on! Let's have
one big adventure!

489
00:36:58,120 --> 00:37:01,317
Come on! Get up there and
have some fun! Come on, here we go.

490
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:23,076
<i>(engíne splutters ínto actíon)</i>

491
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:30,432
But haven't you got
another car that we... What?

492
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:32,312
Oh, all right. Thanks.

493
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:35,557
Are you sure you can't rent us
that truck out there? I'll pay.

494
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,877
I told you, mister. We can't.
This is our first week open.

495
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:42,390
How could we do without our truck?
We're in business.

496
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,476
If we tell the Englishman about...

497
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:47,398
How can you admit
we're involved in anything so hideous?

498
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:51,479
- He'll say he's entitled to a share!
- He would be if he drove us there.

499
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:54,831
And if we don't tell him all about it,
he won't drive us there.

500
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:56,996
Oh, you're such a genius.

501
00:37:57,600 --> 00:38:01,673
Listen! Only ten per cent! There's no
reason why he should expect any more!

502
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:17,436
Thanks for stoppin'.
Listen, can you give me a lift?

503
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:20,711
What's with the little kiddy bicycle?
Are you some kind of a nut?

504
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:24,150
No. I had an accident.
Look, I gotta get to Santa Rosita fast.

505
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:28,717
- I can't help you. I'm turning off soon.
- Wait a minute. Let me just think.

506
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:32,116
I gotta tell somebody. Look,
can you spare a couple of hours?

507
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:36,472
Couple of hours? You've been out in the
sun too long. You're startin' to crack up.

508
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:39,831
No, wait a minute. Listen.
Just hear me out.

509
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:45,392
Now, what I'm gonna tell ya, you just
ain't gonna believe it coulda happened.

510
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:48,956
But there was an accident
a little while back, about 20 miles back.

511
00:38:49,080 --> 00:38:51,799
It involved $350,000.

512
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:57,870
Like I say, when I tell you this, you just
ain't gonna believe it coulda happened.

513
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:01,433
Well... try me. I'm pretty gullible.

514
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,436
<i>(engíne falters)</i>

515
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:45,036
What bothers me is this big W. Are you
sure you told me all you know about it?

516
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:47,469
You don't know what
that guy meant by the big W?

517
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:50,876
No, but none of 'em know.
It's just who gets there and first.

518
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:53,434
Well, what do you say? Is it a deal?

519
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:56,557
Deal!

520
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:58,079
<i>(starts engíne)</i>

521
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:03,149
Oh, you better get that bike outta there.
Somebody might trip over it in the dark.

522
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,636
<i>(tyre bursts)</i>

523
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:17,676
<i>(car horn)</i>

524
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:23,597
Fellas, I'm glad you're here.
Look, I need your help.

525
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:27,759
I had this blowout. The spare may be
a little flat. Take a look at it, will you?

526
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:29,711
Is there an airport near here?

527
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:32,434
If the spare is flat, don't fix it.
Gimme a new tyre.

528
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:36,155
Ain't got a new tyre? Then fix the spare.
But don't look at me. Move it.

529
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:41,912
You can be gassin' up while he's workin'.
What is it, a staring contest? Come on!

530
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:44,231
The pension in my grade...

531
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:48,911
...has not been up
one red cent since 1934!

532
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:51,995
Now, Al...

533
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:54,839
...if the mayor
will get behind a resolution...

534
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:57,428
But I can't put any pressure on the mayor.

535
00:41:57,560 --> 00:42:01,155
You can. You can, Al!
That's the whole point!

536
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:06,593
This case I'll have finished by tonight. It's
one of the biggest cases we've ever had.

537
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:08,676
I want you to tell the mayor about it.

538
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:12,793
Tell him! Tell him the money is
right here where I always said it was!

539
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:14,911
Right in this neighbourhood!

540
00:42:15,040 --> 00:42:18,635
And tell him what credit is gonna be
reflected upon the department!

541
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:22,719
Now, come on, Aloysius. Get in there
and pitch a little for me, will ya?

542
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:25,115
Well, I can try.

543
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,549
Yeah. And he'll listen to ya.

544
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:31,912
And if he gets behind this,
it'll pass unanimously.

545
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:35,794
Now, you know...
you know, Al, I got it comin'.

546
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:38,639
Well, I'll do everything I can.

547
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:40,716
- You know that, don't you?
- Yes.

548
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:47,154
Now, there's just one other little thing
about... No, nothing. Vacation.

549
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:51,068
Once I get Smiler Grogan out of the way,
my desk is clear.

550
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:56,399
I'd like to take a three-week vacation.
Take Ginger on a real nice holiday.

551
00:42:56,520 --> 00:42:59,353
- Is that all right with you?
- Of course it's all right.

552
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:01,755
Thanks. I can hardly wait to tell her.

553
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:06,078
- And you won't forget about the mayor?
- No, no. I'll do my best.

554
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:08,316
I promise you that.

555
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:11,000
Aloysius, I'll never forget you for this.

556
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:16,319
You know, Al, I got a feeling this morning
that everything's comin' my way.

557
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:18,749
<i>(AI chuckles)</i>

558
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:26,599
Sylvester!

559
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:29,836
<i>(scream)</i>

560
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:35,074
- What on earth did you do that for?
- Mummy!

561
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:38,112
Do you have to scare everybody
out of their wits?

562
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:42,392
Why didn't I think? We've been running
around like lunatics, and all the time...

563
00:43:42,520 --> 00:43:46,513
Why didn't I think about Sylvester?
He lives on Silver Strand Beach!

564
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:49,552
- Hey, I never thought of that.
- Who on earth is Sylvester?

565
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:52,274
My son. Emmeline's brother.
He's a lifeguard there.

566
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:55,631
I'm not at all certain
that you haven't damaged this machine.

567
00:44:00,440 --> 00:44:03,955
Oh, kid, don't polish it. This is
one of a fleet of cars. Don't bother.

568
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:07,789
You did a good job. You boys
have a drink on me. Keep the change.

569
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:10,309
- Will you let me get out of here now?
- You!

570
00:44:10,440 --> 00:44:13,796
Oh, no! It's that lunatic who escaped
from the asylum last night!

571
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:16,150
Watch him! He's a homicidal maniac!

572
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:18,589
Get on the phone!
Yell "mayday" on the phone!

573
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:21,280
Listen to me. I'm a psychiatrist.
This man is insane.

574
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:25,393
I'm not your nurse. He has
a hate complex. Calm down, calm down.

575
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:29,513
So, somebody'll stumble over
the little girl's bicycle in the dark, huh?

576
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:33,315
Well, when I finish with you, they'll be
stumbling over <i>you</i> in the dark!

577
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,476
Get on the phone. Get on the phone!

578
00:44:41,920 --> 00:44:43,876
Look, I was clowning.

579
00:44:45,360 --> 00:44:48,557
Sir, wait! You got this...
Why don't you stop... Get some...

580
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:52,275
- I'll kill ya! I'll kill ya!
- I'll buy you a new bicycle!

581
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:54,516
- Look, mister, you got this...
- <i>(growls)</i>

582
00:44:55,120 --> 00:44:57,953
Don't take it so... Will you stop...

583
00:44:58,080 --> 00:45:00,833
Get out of... This is too much.

584
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,916
Look, gimme a break. He's crazy!

585
00:45:03,960 --> 00:45:05,518
Ray!

586
00:45:07,480 --> 00:45:09,436
Get outta here!

587
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:12,154
Stop that! Stop that! He's crazy!

588
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:16,872
Hey, very good. Quick thinkin'.
I'm proud of you, kid.

589
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:21,676
Now tie him up and I'll have a couple
of orderlies come by with a straitjacket.

590
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,756
- Very good.
- I never saw anything.

591
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:25,916
Hey, how many people has he killed?

592
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:29,953
Don't be morbid. Just tie him up until
the boys in the white jackets get here.

593
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:34,358
You did a real good job. Very good.
Look me up. I'm in the book. Dr Zilman.

594
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:41,517
- Sir, we've just got to get to Santa Rosita.
- This is a club. We don't do charter work.

595
00:45:41,640 --> 00:45:43,756
Hey, whose plane is that over there?

596
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:47,236
It belongs to Tyler Fitzgerald.
But he's not going anywhere today.

597
00:45:47,360 --> 00:45:50,272
- Is he here?
- Mr Fitzgerald's in the billiard room.

598
00:45:50,400 --> 00:45:52,436
He's... asleep. Nobody can talk to him.

599
00:45:52,560 --> 00:45:54,949
- Can we just ask him a question?
- <i>(phone ríngs)</i>

600
00:45:55,080 --> 00:45:56,991
No, you can't!

601
00:45:57,120 --> 00:45:59,315
Hello. Wait a minute. Wait a minute!

602
00:46:02,880 --> 00:46:06,190
Come on, Benjy. That must be
Mr Fitzgerald over there!

603
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:09,551
- You can't disturb Mr Fitzgerald.
- We just wanna talk to him.

604
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:11,636
- Let him rest, please.
- Mr Fitzgerald.

605
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:14,194
- Shh.
- Don't shush me. We wanna talk to him.

606
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:17,039
Just a moment.
Wake up, please, Mr Fitzgerald.

607
00:46:17,160 --> 00:46:19,993
- <i>(snoríng)</i>
- I think he's got a cold.

608
00:46:20,120 --> 00:46:23,476
No, Mr Fitzgerald, listen. Please, sir.

609
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:26,558
We hate to disturb your sleep,
but this is an emergency.

610
00:46:26,680 --> 00:46:29,114
You have no right to crash in here.

611
00:46:29,240 --> 00:46:30,798
<i>(coughíng)</i>

612
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:33,354
- Oh, that's a head cold.
- Mr Fitzgerald, listen.

613
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:36,950
You know Rosita Beach?
You're the only one who can get us there.

614
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:40,436
- And it's a matter of life and death!
- Yes, a matter of life and death!

615
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:43,074
- Our grandmother is dying.
- Who's dying?

616
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:45,998
Our grandmother is dying
and she sent for us.

617
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:50,272
Yeah. She's in Rosita Beach, see?
She's dying, and we're up here...

618
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:53,790
...and she'd kinda like to have us
be with her when she goes.

619
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:55,751
Otherwise, she won't go.

620
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:59,111
- Oh, she'll go, but...
- Sorry, sir. They forced their way in.

621
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:03,950
No, we didn't. Let me introduce myself.
I'm Dingy Bell. This is Benjy Benjamin.

622
00:47:04,080 --> 00:47:06,514
- How do you do?
- Oh, stop with that already!

623
00:47:06,640 --> 00:47:10,872
Look, sir. We'd like for you
to help us out by taking us down...

624
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:14,871
- What's the matter?
- Wait a minute. Just a minute!

625
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:17,116
- Yes, I... I can't see.
- What?

626
00:47:17,240 --> 00:47:20,437
Something's happened to my eyes.
I... I... I can't see.

627
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:23,199
- You can't see? He can't see.
- Must be an eye cold.

628
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:27,029
- George... George, I can't see!
- One minute, Mr Fitzgerald.

629
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:30,391
I can't see! George... George, I...

630
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:33,038
Aaarghhh!

631
00:47:33,720 --> 00:47:34,596
Mr Fitzgerald!

632
00:47:36,120 --> 00:47:38,509
We wanna make sure
he doesn't get loose.

633
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:44,154
I'll kill that dirty, rotten bum
when I get my hands on him.

634
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:47,678
What's the matter?
How come I'm all tied up like this?

635
00:47:47,800 --> 00:47:52,555
- Just sit there. Everything'll be all right.
- Friends will come and take care of you.

636
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:55,035
What friends? What are you talkin' about?

637
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:58,835
- Get this stuff off me. Turn me loose.
- Take it easy, pal. You've been sick.

638
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:02,873
Who's been sick? And where's
that bum with the glasses, huh?

639
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:05,992
Now just sit still because
the doctor's gone to get help.

640
00:48:06,120 --> 00:48:09,669
What doctor? I don't know no doctor.
Are you guys crazy?

641
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:13,634
I'm warnin' you, get this stuff off me.
Understand? Get this stuff off me!

642
00:48:13,760 --> 00:48:17,150
- Watch him. Ray, watch him!
- I'm warning you...

643
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:19,236
I'm gonna have to hit you again!

644
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:21,476
Ow! Argh!

645
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:23,875
<i>(lrwín)</i> My arm! You broke my arm!

646
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:25,956
<i>(grunts)</i>

647
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:41,717
Now, fellas, you keep this up,
and I'm gonna get sore.

648
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:51,678
OK. If that's the way you want it,
that's the way you're gonna get it.

649
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:59,556
Oh! Put me down!

650
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:01,636
I'll kill ya!

651
00:49:01,760 --> 00:49:03,671
- Help!
- He's ruinin' our place!

652
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:05,756
Come on, Ray.

653
00:49:15,480 --> 00:49:18,597
- <i>(Ray)</i> You better get outta here, mister!
- Leave us alone!

654
00:49:18,720 --> 00:49:20,676
Aargh!

655
00:49:23,920 --> 00:49:27,674
- Uh-huh. There you are.
- <i>(Ray)</i> What are we gonna do?

656
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:31,798
Dr Zilman! Dr Zilman!

657
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:38,713
Aaaargh!

658
00:49:42,760 --> 00:49:45,911
Help! Put me down! You put me down!

659
00:49:46,040 --> 00:49:47,996
Put me down immediately!

660
00:49:49,640 --> 00:49:52,029
- Aaargh!
- If that's the way you want it...

661
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:55,550
...you're gonna get it that way.
- He-e-e-elp!

662
00:50:00,600 --> 00:50:03,956
- Ray! Are you all right?
- I'm fine. I'm OK.

663
00:50:08,640 --> 00:50:12,189
Listen, guys. You're gettin' outta line.
I've had all I can take.

664
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:14,788
