01:55:48,520 --> 01:55:51,432
Now run on back to headquarters.
Wait to hear from me.

1516
01:55:51,560 --> 01:55:56,156
- Let me go with you, Chief.
- No. It might snarl things up a little.

1517
01:55:56,280 --> 01:55:58,236
Thanks for everything.

1518
01:55:58,360 --> 01:56:00,316
Lots of luck, Chief.

1519
01:56:33,320 --> 01:56:36,278
Hey, Benjy! Did you see anything, pal?

1520
01:56:36,400 --> 01:56:39,233
No, but there must be
somethin' somewhere.

1521
01:56:39,360 --> 01:56:41,590
Hey, hey. Hey!

1522
01:56:42,520 --> 01:56:44,272
- Did you see anything?
- Nothing.

1523
01:56:44,400 --> 01:56:47,472
Are you sure he didn't say
something else and you've forgotten?

1524
01:56:47,600 --> 01:56:51,275
Look, he said it would be buried
under a big W and that we'd see it.

1525
01:56:51,400 --> 01:56:53,436
- It's gotta be here.
- I'll tell you what.

1526
01:56:53,560 --> 01:56:57,109
You go the way we came, and we'll go
the way you came, in case we missed it.

1527
01:56:57,240 --> 01:56:59,117
Hold it.

1528
01:56:59,240 --> 01:57:01,196
You go the way we came, and we'll go...

1529
01:57:01,320 --> 01:57:03,276
That's right. OK, let's go.

1530
01:57:10,480 --> 01:57:15,554
They're lookin' for somethin' buried
under "a big W". I heard one of 'em say it.

1531
01:57:15,680 --> 01:57:17,830
Yeah, I heard. But what?

1532
01:58:04,400 --> 01:58:06,868
- Hey!
- <i>(Díng)</i> Did you see anything yet?

1533
01:58:07,000 --> 01:58:08,319
- No. Did you?
- Nothing.

1534
01:58:08,440 --> 01:58:11,910
That guy hid it so good, I bet
he couldn't even find it himself.

1535
01:58:21,920 --> 01:58:24,036
- Who's he?
- I don't know.

1536
01:58:24,160 --> 01:58:27,277
- Well, he had a shovel.
- Maybe he was a prospector.

1537
01:58:27,400 --> 01:58:29,516
- What do you mean?
- We're wasting time.

1538
01:58:29,640 --> 01:58:34,077
- Harder! We gotta look harder!
- Let's look harder. Come on, let's go!

1539
01:58:45,440 --> 01:58:48,512
- Who's he?
- I don't know, but he hasn't got a shovel.

1540
01:58:56,320 --> 01:59:00,279
He's here! That's his car!
Wait till I get my hands on that phony.

1541
01:59:00,400 --> 01:59:03,551
Somebody came in those cabs!
Let's get movin', man!

1542
01:59:03,680 --> 01:59:06,069
- Let's get movin'.
- They must still be here.

1543
01:59:06,200 --> 01:59:09,590
They'd better be! Come on, Emmeline.
You're not just gonna sit there?

1544
01:59:09,720 --> 01:59:12,553
- You're not just gonna sit there?
- Yes, I am.

1545
01:59:12,680 --> 01:59:14,671
Then sit, Emmeline!

1546
01:59:14,800 --> 01:59:17,598
Mrs Finch, aren't you
the teeniest bit curious?

1547
01:59:17,720 --> 01:59:21,599
No, I am not even curious,
Mr Hawthorne. Just disgusted.

1548
01:59:21,720 --> 01:59:23,517
Oh, I say, that really is a pity.

1549
01:59:23,640 --> 01:59:25,596
You'll forgive me, I must go.

1550
01:59:32,480 --> 01:59:34,436
<i>(whísperíng)</i> Hey!

1551
01:59:34,720 --> 01:59:38,429
<i>(Mrs Marcus)</i> You wouldn't know
a big W if you saw one!

1552
01:59:38,800 --> 01:59:41,155
I don't think they've gotten here yet.

1553
01:59:41,280 --> 01:59:43,714
They're here somewhere,
so they haven't found it.

1554
01:59:43,840 --> 01:59:46,274
You sure that guy just said
buried under a big W?

1555
01:59:46,400 --> 01:59:50,916
- Actually, I joined the party after that.
- Yes, that's what he said. Under a big W.

1556
01:59:51,040 --> 01:59:55,238
- <i>(Fínch)</i> Let's look over there.
- <i>(Mrs Marcus)</i> Shut up and follow me.

1557
01:59:55,360 --> 01:59:57,316
<i>(bíckeríng contínues)</i>

1558
02:00:18,360 --> 02:00:20,316
<i>(stíll bíckeríng)</i>

1559
02:00:46,680 --> 02:00:49,353
- Who are they? From this morning?
- Yeah.

1560
02:00:52,200 --> 02:00:54,156
- Who's he?
- I don't know.

1561
02:00:55,760 --> 02:00:57,193
- Who's <i>he?</i>
- I don't know!

1562
02:00:57,320 --> 02:01:00,278
Mama, how many people
are mixed up in this thing?

1563
02:01:01,440 --> 02:01:02,919
Mama, who are they?

1564
02:01:03,040 --> 02:01:05,918
Cabbies? Mama,
this thing's like a convention!

1565
02:01:41,280 --> 02:01:44,238
Is anything wrong, ma'am?
I didn't mean to startle you.

1566
02:01:44,360 --> 02:01:47,875
Who are you? Are you with the others?
The ones that are looking?

1567
02:01:48,000 --> 02:01:50,230
- Well, I am, in a way. Aren't you?
- No!

1568
02:01:50,360 --> 02:01:53,989
I didn't want to have anything
to do with it right from the start.

1569
02:01:54,120 --> 02:01:56,918
And you know what? I know where it is.

1570
02:01:57,040 --> 02:01:59,998
I'm the only one that knows,
and I wasn't even looking!

1571
02:02:00,120 --> 02:02:03,396
- You know where it is?
- Yes. I don't know what I should do.

1572
02:02:04,960 --> 02:02:06,678
Agh!

1573
02:02:06,800 --> 02:02:10,713
- Come out, all of you! This is ridiculous!
- I absolutely agree, Mrs Marcus.

1574
02:02:10,840 --> 02:02:13,798
We all know we're all here,
and nobody's fooling anybody.

1575
02:02:13,920 --> 02:02:16,878
- So we all know! So what?
- Don't talk to my mama that way!

1576
02:02:17,000 --> 02:02:18,149
- You hear?
- You hear?

1577
02:02:18,280 --> 02:02:21,238
- <i>(Mrs Marcus)</i> Shut up!
- We ain't the only ones here.

1578
02:02:21,360 --> 02:02:24,511
- I seen four or five other guys.
- Yeah. Those two cab drivers.

1579
02:02:24,640 --> 02:02:27,473
- They came with us, and that dentist.
- You wanna start?

1580
02:02:27,600 --> 02:02:30,592
- Yes, I wanna start!
- Why are we wasting so much time?

1581
02:02:30,720 --> 02:02:34,349
We all know that we're all here,
and even if somebody finds the money...

1582
02:02:34,480 --> 02:02:37,790
...nobody's gonna get away with it
unless everybody gets a share.

1583
02:02:37,920 --> 02:02:40,673
So let's get sensible
and get this thing organised!

1584
02:02:40,800 --> 02:02:43,394
- Did you all hear what Mama said?
- Yeah.

1585
02:02:43,520 --> 02:02:44,873
Come on, Mama.

1586
02:02:45,000 --> 02:02:49,312
Now wait a minute. Did any of you...
anybody see a guy with glasses...

1587
02:02:49,440 --> 02:02:51,874
...with a real sneery
expression on his face?

1588
02:02:52,000 --> 02:02:54,992
I mean, this guy was ugly.
I mean, like, real ugly.

1589
02:02:59,480 --> 02:03:03,268
And if you help me dig it up,
you can have half and I'll have half.

1590
02:03:03,400 --> 02:03:05,789
Is that OK? I mean, is that fair?

1591
02:03:06,680 --> 02:03:09,069
Because if I have half of the money...

1592
02:03:09,200 --> 02:03:12,909
...I can go away somewhere
where nobody can find me.

1593
02:03:13,040 --> 02:03:16,953
Not Russell, or my mother,
or Sylvester - anybody.

1594
02:03:18,080 --> 02:03:20,275
You don't know what that'd mean.

1595
02:03:20,400 --> 02:03:25,155
Why, if I had enough money, I might even
be able to live in a convent or something.

1596
02:03:25,280 --> 02:03:27,350
- In a convent?
- Uh-huh.

1597
02:03:27,680 --> 02:03:29,830
Now, we all know
that we're all here. Right?

1598
02:03:29,960 --> 02:03:34,397
It seems intelligent to me that we should
all share in one equal share apiece.

1599
02:03:34,520 --> 02:03:36,112
- Is that right?
- He's right.

1600
02:03:36,240 --> 02:03:38,595
- So we all know that! Look...
- <i>(clunk)</i>

1601
02:03:39,480 --> 02:03:41,436
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yeah!

1602
02:03:41,560 --> 02:03:43,710
It's him, all right. Yeah!

1603
02:03:45,080 --> 02:03:47,469
You got this wrong! I came to apologise!

1604
02:03:47,600 --> 02:03:49,875
Forgive and forget! I'm your friend!

1605
02:03:50,040 --> 02:03:52,270
Oh, no, you got me... Oh, he's so neurotic!

1606
02:03:52,400 --> 02:03:54,516
- Can't you do something?
- I'll get ya!

1607
02:03:54,640 --> 02:03:58,997
- He's very neurotic. I'm your friend!
- If I get my hands on you, I'II...

1608
02:04:10,240 --> 02:04:11,719
Why, that's it!

1609
02:04:11,840 --> 02:04:13,637
Sure! Look!

1610
02:04:13,760 --> 02:04:15,910
It's the big W, I tell ya!

1611
02:04:16,040 --> 02:04:17,996
It's the big W!

1612
02:04:20,080 --> 02:04:22,036
Look at this! Look at it!

1613
02:04:22,160 --> 02:04:24,116
<i>(all talk excítedly)</i>

1614
02:04:28,160 --> 02:04:33,314
I'm sorry, Mrs Finch.
I'm afraid it's too late.

1615
02:04:33,440 --> 02:04:35,396
I think they've found it.

1616
02:04:41,760 --> 02:04:43,716
Folks, isn't this great?!

1617
02:04:44,400 --> 02:04:47,039
Congratulations. Well done!

1618
02:04:47,160 --> 02:04:50,709
Listen. I think the big boy here
should get an extra share from all of us.

1619
02:04:50,840 --> 02:04:52,831
After all, it was he who found it.

1620
02:04:52,960 --> 02:04:56,191
Yes, I insist. He gets an extra share.

1621
02:04:56,320 --> 02:04:59,357
- <i>(Fínch)</i> Yes. He deserves an extra share.
- Well, I...

1622
02:04:59,480 --> 02:05:03,029
- Let's start diggin'.
- If somebody comes, what'll we tell 'em?

1623
02:05:03,160 --> 02:05:06,869
We could say we're here
with an anthropological expedition.

1624
02:05:07,000 --> 02:05:10,310
We tell 'em to hit the road
or we'll beat their brains in!

1625
02:05:11,040 --> 02:05:12,996
Well, it was a nice dream.

1626
02:05:14,120 --> 02:05:16,076
It lasted almost five minutes.

1627
02:05:25,640 --> 02:05:27,756
- Don't bug me, I said!
- Tell him to dig!

1628
02:05:27,880 --> 02:05:31,395
<i>(whísperíng)</i> Faster.
Come on, Sylvester. Dig, dig.

1629
02:05:31,520 --> 02:05:33,715
Faster. Faster.

1630
02:05:33,840 --> 02:05:36,274
Faster. Dig. That's it. Dig.

1631
02:06:29,040 --> 02:06:30,155
Faster.

1632
02:06:41,480 --> 02:06:46,235
Hey, come on. There's not enough room!
There's not enough room! You two, out.

1633
02:06:53,920 --> 02:06:55,876
Wait a minute! There's not enough room!

1634
02:06:56,000 --> 02:06:58,594
- And you're buggin' me!
- What do you mean, buggin'?

1635
02:06:58,720 --> 02:07:00,438
- Cut out.
- What is this "cut out"?

1636
02:07:00,560 --> 02:07:03,358
- Out, baby. Out, baby, out!
- Don't call me "baby".

1637
02:07:03,480 --> 02:07:05,436
- Quit arguing!
- <i>(all argue)</i>

1638
02:07:08,080 --> 02:07:10,036
<i>(díggíng contínues)</i>

1639
02:07:16,360 --> 02:07:18,715
- <i>(clunk)</i>
- What's that? What was that?

1640
02:07:20,760 --> 02:07:22,716
It sounded like it hit a chest.

1641
02:07:22,840 --> 02:07:24,796
<i>(all talk at once)</i>

1642
02:07:30,240 --> 02:07:34,028
Scrape the dirt away.
Get the dirt out of it. Use your hands.

1643
02:07:38,520 --> 02:07:40,272
It's a satchel!

1644
02:07:40,400 --> 02:07:43,836
- I got it. I got it.
- Open it. Open it up.

1645
02:07:43,960 --> 02:07:45,916
Quick! Come on!

1646
02:07:48,120 --> 02:07:50,076
- <i>(Benjy)</i> Bingo!
- That's it!

1647
02:07:50,200 --> 02:07:52,953
I say, chaps, shouldn't we
find a spot of cover?

1648
02:07:53,080 --> 02:07:55,833
- No! There's nobody around.
- Come on. Count it out.

1649
02:07:55,960 --> 02:07:58,076
- What are we waiting for?
- Wait a second!

1650
02:07:58,200 --> 02:08:02,432
Everybody's gonna get somethin', so no
arguments, cos we'll get an equal share!

1651
02:08:02,920 --> 02:08:05,309
He's right. That's the only way to do it.

1652
02:08:05,440 --> 02:08:08,079
Shares for everybody!
Now, how many are we?

1653
02:08:09,040 --> 02:08:12,999
One, two, three, four, five...

1654
02:08:13,120 --> 02:08:14,951
...six, seven, eight...

1655
02:08:15,880 --> 02:08:19,589
...nine, ten, eleven, twelve...

1656
02:08:19,720 --> 02:08:22,632
...thirteen, fourteen, fifteen.

1657
02:08:22,760 --> 02:08:27,311
- Fifteen of us. That's fifteen equal shares.
- Why, you dirty double-crosser!

1658
02:08:27,440 --> 02:08:30,989
- You cut yourself in twice!
- You can't get away with that!

1659
02:08:32,600 --> 02:08:34,556
Grab him! Grab him! Get him!

1660
02:08:37,280 --> 02:08:40,511
You didn't cheat anybody but yourself
because now <i>you're</i> out!

1661
02:08:40,640 --> 02:08:42,596
Listen. Listen!

1662
02:08:42,720 --> 02:08:46,076
You can't cut me out now!
Not after what I've been through!

1663
02:08:47,240 --> 02:08:48,593
All right. OK.

1664
02:08:48,720 --> 02:08:52,633
I'm warnin' ya, if I don't get a share,
I'm gonna go straight to the police!

1665
02:08:52,760 --> 02:08:54,990
- The police?
- Look here, you rotter...

1666
02:08:55,120 --> 02:08:58,635
Yap yap yap yap! That money
had to come from somewhere!

1667
02:08:58,760 --> 02:09:03,117
It come from that poor old man who died
up on the mountain this morning.

1668
02:09:03,240 --> 02:09:06,949
- You wasn't even there, so shut up!
- All right. OK. You asked for it.

1669
02:09:07,080 --> 02:09:08,957
I'm gonna go straight to the police!

1670
02:09:09,080 --> 02:09:11,594
Why would the police
be interested, Mr Meyer?

1671
02:09:11,720 --> 02:09:14,154
Are you kiddin'? Isn't it obvious?

1672
02:09:14,280 --> 02:09:16,236
How do you think money gets...

1673
02:09:19,000 --> 02:09:21,992
- How did you know my name?
- Do you know this crook?

1674
02:09:22,440 --> 02:09:26,797
Well, I've never actually met him, Mr Pike,
but I've come to feel that I know him.

1675
02:09:27,680 --> 02:09:30,717
How do you know <i>my</i> name?
I don't believe I've met you.

1676
02:09:31,080 --> 02:09:35,119
Yeah. Who are you? We thought he came
with you. Didn't he come with you?

1677
02:09:35,240 --> 02:09:38,198
He didn't come with <i>us.</i>
We thought he came with <i>you.</i>

1678
02:09:38,320 --> 02:09:41,710
- <i>(Díng)</i> No!
- If he didn't come with you or with us...

1679
02:09:42,520 --> 02:09:44,192
...well, then, who are you?

1680
02:09:44,320 --> 02:09:48,598
I'm Captain Culpeper
of the Santa Rosita Police Department.

1681
02:09:53,560 --> 02:09:56,233
- <i>Wíll you come to the poínt?</i>
- I'm comin' to the point.

1682
02:09:56,360 --> 02:10:00,069
The point is that I happen to have
enough stuff in my private files...

1683
02:10:00,200 --> 02:10:05,752
...stuff relating to civic building, road
contracts, harbour and cannery projects...

1684
02:10:05,880 --> 02:10:09,873
Enough stuff to put you, the DA,
myself and a two-thirds majority...

1685
02:10:10,000 --> 02:10:12,673
...behind bars for the next 20 years.

1686
02:10:12,800 --> 02:10:16,713
And I give you my word that
that's exactly where everybody is going...

1687
02:10:16,840 --> 02:10:19,638
...unless certain things
start happening now!

1688
02:10:19,760 --> 02:10:21,034
<i>Líke what, for ínstance?</i>

1689
02:10:21,160 --> 02:10:25,836
I want the pension for Culpeper's grade
trebled! Not doubled - trebled!

1690
02:10:25,960 --> 02:10:28,394
I want Culpeper to retire with honour.

1691
02:10:28,520 --> 02:10:32,559
I want it on paper and signed
that that's exactly what's gonna happen...

1692
02:10:32,680 --> 02:10:35,240
...and I want that paper in my hands
in 15 minutes...

1693
02:10:35,360 --> 02:10:38,909
...or I'll have all the reporters in town
in here in 20.

1694
02:10:39,040 --> 02:10:43,113
Now, you know the word for this,
Your Honour. It's called blackmail.

1695
02:11:00,640 --> 02:11:04,394
Sir, could you possibly see your way
clear to... give us a break?

1696
02:11:04,520 --> 02:11:06,511
You kiddin'? Him give you a break?

1697
02:11:06,960 --> 02:11:12,318
We had a rough day already. We was all
covered in dirt and fell down in a plane...

1698
02:11:12,440 --> 02:11:15,637
...and my grandmother's dying in Oxnard.

1699
02:11:15,880 --> 02:11:19,031
I know we don't deserve
any kindness, Captain, but...

1700
02:11:19,160 --> 02:11:23,711
...if you could help us, I'm sure we'd all
be inspired to go on and live better lives.

1701
02:11:24,080 --> 02:11:26,753
Well, there is one thing.

1702
02:11:26,880 --> 02:11:29,189
I don't know whether it would help or not.

1703
02:11:29,320 --> 02:11:33,518
But... if, instead of <i>my</i> turning you in...

1704
02:11:33,640 --> 02:11:36,108
...you went and turned yourselves in...

1705
02:11:36,240 --> 02:11:39,869
...juries sometimes look
very favourably on things like that.

1706
02:11:40,000 --> 02:11:42,195
You... You'd let us do that?

1707
02:11:42,320 --> 02:11:44,709
What are we waiting for?
Let's turn ourselves in.

1708
02:11:44,840 --> 02:11:49,311
You're a fine human being, sir. After all,
why should you care if we get a break?

1709
02:11:49,440 --> 02:11:54,560
Well, Mr Meyer, no matter what you've all
done today, you're not really criminals.

1710
02:11:55,800 --> 02:12:01,716
So, if you like, you can all hop into those
two cabs and drive over to Santa Rosita...

1711
02:12:01,840 --> 02:12:04,832
...and, uh... just walk in.

1712
02:12:04,960 --> 02:12:08,509
- Then let's do that.
- But we can't all get into the two cabs.

1713
02:12:08,640 --> 02:12:12,713
You can't take the stolen vehicles. Those
have to stay here to be picked up later.

1714
02:12:12,840 --> 02:12:15,400
Well, let's go before he changes his mind.

1715
02:12:15,520 --> 02:12:17,476
<i>(all talkíng at once)</i>

1716
02:12:22,080 --> 02:12:25,675
Drive carefully. They may be
the last passengers you'll ever carry.

1717
02:12:25,800 --> 02:12:28,598
Oh, funny. That's funny.
Funny, right? Funny?

1718
02:12:28,720 --> 02:12:31,393
You could be the most comical cop
I ever met.

1719
02:12:31,520 --> 02:12:33,272
Yeah!

1720
02:12:59,000 --> 02:13:00,956
- Culpeper.
- <i>Yes, sír?</i>

1721
02:13:01,800 --> 02:13:03,995
Everything is under control here.

1722
02:13:04,120 --> 02:13:09,638
It'll take a little longer because there was
a joker that nobody knew about. Right?

1723
02:13:09,760 --> 02:13:11,398
<i>Yes, sír.</i>

1724
02:13:11,520 --> 02:13:14,512
So don't make a move of any kind
until you hear from me.

1725
02:13:14,640 --> 02:13:16,392
<i>Yes, sír.</i>

1726
02:13:22,480 --> 02:13:26,871
Listen. Why does the man wanna give
everybody a break? What's his angle?

1727
02:13:27,000 --> 02:13:30,959
- Yeah. I was wondering about that too.
- Somethin' very funny is goin' on.

